MBOMBELA – A storm wreaked havoc on the R40 Barberton Road last night after a tree fell on a car, and roofs were blown off homes.  J&M Security’s Nico van Aswegen and his family were driving home on a dirt road when a tree fell onto their vehicle.  J&M’s Security’s Hendrick Botha said Van Aswegan had sustained minor head injuries, but was discharged from hospital this morning. “His family was with him in the car, but luckily they were not injured.” ALSO READ: BREAKING NEWS: Three people killed after a collision on N4 near Ngodwana Damage to a house on the R40.  Damage at Pro-Life’s kennels A house which was damaged during the storm. 